# 🔐 Secure File Locker in C

A simple yet powerful **file encryption and decryption tool** written in
C using XOR-based encryption and HEX encoding.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 🚀 Features

-   🔑 Password-based encryption
-   🔓 Decryption using the same password
-   🔄 Uses XOR encryption (reversible)
-   🧾 Encrypted output stored in readable HEX format
-   💻 Command-line interface (CLI)
-   ⚡ Fast and lightweight

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 🧠 How It Works

-   Each character of the file is XOR-ed with a password key
-   The result is converted into HEX format for safe storage
-   During decryption, HEX is converted back and XOR is applied again to
    recover original data

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 📂 Project Structure

file-locker/ │ ├── main.c ├── encrypt.c ├── encrypt.h ├── README.md

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 🔧 Compilation

gcc main.c encrypt.c -o locker

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## ▶️ Usage

### 🔐 Encrypt a file

locker input.txt encrypted.txt mypassword e

### 🔓 Decrypt a file

locker encrypted.txt decrypted.txt mypassword d

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 📌 Arguments

-   input : Input file name\
-   output : Output file name\
-   password: Encryption/Decryption key\
-   mode : e (encrypt), d (decrypt)

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 💡 Example

Input: Hello World\
Encrypted: 1F0A0F0F08...\
Decrypted: Hello World

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## ⚠️ Notes

-   Same password must be used for decryption
-   Encrypted file is stored in HEX format
-   This is for learning purposes

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 🔥 Future Improvements

-   Stronger encryption
-   Base64 support
-   GUI version

